ECLOGUE VII.

THIS is a strictly bucolic poem, imitated from the sixth Idyl of Theocri- tus, The herdsman Meliboeus relates a contest in verse between the shepherds Corydon and Thyrsis with Daphnis sor umpire. The scene is apparently laid in the pastoral region of North Italy. The date assigned to it is nc. 38.

MELIBOEUS. CORYDON. THYRSIS.
